Blending styles from roots, rock, folk, soul, and Americana, Aaron has put together a band that will have crowds from coffee shops to large venues singing and dancing.
A Seattle native, Aaron taught himself how to play the guitar by studying Pete Townshend, John Butler, Paul Simon, and Eddie Vedder. In 2006 Aaron moved to Montana and began playing in bars and saloons honing his songwriting abilities. After 4 years in Big Sky country Aaron moved to San Francisco and dove head first into the music scene. Over the next 5 years he played in multiple bands and toured up and down the west coast. In the spring of 2014 Aaron recorded his debut EP in Berkeley’s legendary Fantasy Studios (Alum’s include Green Day, Herbie Hancock, U2). “The Lucid Whiskey EP” was released in the summer of 2014 and received a large amount of online praise. Aaron then embarked on an extensive solo tour promoting the record. His Seattle show was so well received and the response was so enthusiastic, Aaron decided to move back home.
Once back in the Pacific Northwest Aaron found himself surrounded by old high school friends, many of whom were now some of the best musicians in Seattle. Thus Lindstrom and The Limit was created.
